{
  "doc_id": "54268",
  "text": "The role of the inflammasome components NLRP3 and ASC in CS models has not been fully investigated. However, there is evidence of inflammasome activation, since levels of caspase-1 are increased in lung tissue after CS challenge in mice. Caspase-1 levels are also higher in lung tissue from COPD patients and smokers than from nonsmoking donors [CITATION_1] . Selective inhibition of caspase-1 significantly decreased inflammation after CS challenge in animal models [CITATION_2] . These data support a role for the inflammasome in the airway inflammation in COPD and asthma, although further studies are required.",
